Contextual Intent & Temporal API
================================

FastAPI service that turns a clinical query into intents, representative
terms, and retrieval signals (record types + temporal). It wraps intent.py.
Runs on GCP (Cloud Run) and calls Gemini on Vertex AI.


How it works (the prompts)
--------------------------
One request runs 3 LLM calls, or 4 when retrieval signals are requested.
Each call is a separate prompt with a fixed job.

Step 1 - Expand the query          (QUERY_EXPANSION_PROMPT)
  Raw query -> fuller clinical version. Spells out abbreviations
  (DM -> Diabetes Mellitus) and expands broad terms into specifics
  (vitals -> blood pressure, heart rate, temp...). Everything after this
  step reads the expanded query.

Steps 2 and 3 run in parallel, both off the expanded query:

Step 2 - Extract intents           (INTENT_EXTRACTION_PROMPT)
  The distinct clinical intents. Each has a title, description, nature,
  sub-natures, and the atomic concepts to search for.

Step 3 - Extract representative terms   (REPRESENTATIVE_TERMS_PROMPT)
  The 1-3 canonical entities the query is really about (e.g. "EKG").

Step 4 - Build context / retrieval signals   (CONTEXTUAL_ENVIRONMENT_PROMPT)
  Only when include_retrieval_signals is true. Per concept:
  Task 1 (facets): record types, authors, care-lifecycle, setting.
  Task 2 (temporal): the time window. Reads the query + intent description;
  if neither gives a cue it defaults from the concept type (labs/imaging ->
  recent, chronic -> current, history -> past). Each temporal is matched
  against the vocabulary file to attach a code and formula.


Requirements
------------
- Python 3.11+
- GCP project with Vertex AI (Gemini) enabled
- The vocabulary file temporal_name_to_cui.json in GCS (or on disk locally)


Run locally
-----------
pip install -r requirements.txt
export INTENT_GCP_PROJECT=your-project
export INTENT_API_KEY=some-key
# local credentials for Vertex/GCS:
gcloud auth application-default login
uvicorn intent_api:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080

Docs: /docs   OpenAPI: /openapi.json


Deploy on GCP (Cloud Run)
-------------------------
1. Build and push the image to Artifact Registry:
     gcloud builds submit --tag REGION-docker.pkg.dev/PROJECT/REPO/intent-api:latest

2. Put the vocabulary file in GCS:
     gsutil cp temporal_name_to_cui.json gs://YOUR_BUCKET/path/temporal_name_to_cui.json

3. Store the API key in Secret Manager:
     printf "your-key" | gcloud secrets create intent-api-key --data-file=-

4. Give the service account these roles:
     roles/aiplatform.user               (Gemini on Vertex)
     roles/storage.objectViewer          (read the vocab from GCS)
     roles/secretmanager.secretAccessor  (read the API key)

5. Edit the placeholders in service.yaml and deploy:
     gcloud run services replace service.yaml --region REGION

The attached service account provides Vertex + GCS credentials, so no key
file is needed in the container.


Endpoints
---------
POST /v1/analyze   analyze a query
GET  /healthz      liveness
GET  /readyz       readiness (503 until the pipeline + vocabulary are loaded)


Example
-------
curl -sX POST https://YOUR-SERVICE-URL/v1/analyze \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-API-Key: some-key" \
  -d '{"query":"colonoscopy images and report from the last 6 months","include_retrieval_signals":true}'


Errors
------
{ "error": { "code": "...", "message": "...", "details": null } }

200 ok   401 bad/missing key   422 bad query   502 Gemini failed   503 not ready   504 timeout


Config (env vars; INTENT_GCP_PROJECT and INTENT_API_KEY are the important ones)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INTENT_GCP_PROJECT           GCP project id (required)
INTENT_API_KEY               key clients must send; empty = auth off (dev only)
INTENT_GCP_LOCATION          default us-central1
INTENT_MODEL_NAME            default gemini-2.5-flash
INTENT_TEMPORAL_GCS_BUCKET   GCS bucket holding the vocabulary file
INTENT_TEMPORAL_GCS_PATH     object path of the vocabulary file in that bucket
INTENT_TEMPORAL_FILE         local vocab path, used only if the GCS vars are empty
